<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Mash
<hw>Mash</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Akin to G. <ets>meisch</ets>,
<ets>maisch</ets>, <ets>meische</ets>, <ets>maische</ets>, mash, wash,
and prob. to AS. <ets>miscian</ets> to mix. See <er>Mix</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A mass of mixed ingredients reduced to a soft pulpy
state by beating or pressure; a mass of anything in a soft pulpy state.
Specifically <fld>(Brewing)</fld>, ground or bruised malt, or meal of
rye, wheat, corn, or other grain (or a mixture of malt and meal) steeped
and stirred in hot water for making the wort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mixture of meal or bran and water fed to
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A mess; trouble.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mash tun</b></col>, <cd>a large tub used in making mash
and wort.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Mash
<hw>Mash</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Mashed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mashing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to G. <ets>meischen</ets>,
<ets>maischen</ets>, to mash, mix, and prob. to <ets>mischen</ets>, E.
<ets>mix</ets>. See 2d <er>Mash</er>.]</ety> <def>To convert into a
mash; to reduce to a soft pulpy state by beating or pressure; to bruise;
to crush; <as>as, to <ex>mash</ex> apples in a mill, or potatoes with a
pestle</as>.</def> <specif>Specifically</specif> <fld>(Brewing)</fld>,
<def>to convert, as malt, or malt and meal, into the mash which makes
wort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mashing tub</b></col>, <cd>a tub for making the mash in
breweries and distilleries; -- called also <altname>mash tun</altname>,
and <altname>mash vat</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mashed potato</ent>⟦br⟧
